  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some useful websites for students?",
  "response": "There are many useful websites that can aid students in their academic pursuits, research, and overall learning experience. Here\u2019s a list of some popular and valuable resources:\n\n1. **Khan Academy** (www.khanacademy.org) - Offers free courses in various subjects, including math, science, and humanities, with instructional videos and practice exercises.\n\n2. **Coursera** (www.coursera.org) - Provides access to online courses from universities and institutions worldwide on a wide range of topics.\n\n3. **edX** (www.edx.org) - Features online courses from top universities. Many courses are free to audit, with an option to obtain a certificate for a fee.\n\n4. **Quizlet** (www.quizlet.com) - A study tool that allows students to create flashcards, quizzes, and games for various subjects.\n\n5. **Chegg** (www.chegg.com) - Offers textbook rentals, homework help, and tutoring services, as well as solutions to textbook problems.\n\n6. **Wolfram Alpha** (www.wolframalpha.com) - A computational knowledge engine that can solve mathematical problems and provide data and analysis for various subjects.\n\n7. **Google Scholar** (scholar.google.com) - A search engine specifically for scholarly literature, useful for research papers and academic articles.\n\n8. **Purdue Online Writing Lab (OWL)** (owl.purdue.edu) - Offers writing resources, including grammar guides and citation style manuals for academic writing.\n\n9. **Duolingo** (www.duolingo.com) - A language-learning platform with interactive lessons and exercises for various languages.\n\n10. **Grammarly** (www.grammarly.com) - A writing assistant that checks for grammar, punctuation, and style errors, helping students improve their writing.\n\n11. **Canva** (www.canva.com) - A design tool that allows students to create presentations, posters, and infographics easily.\n\n12. **Kahoot!** (www.kahoot.com) - A game-based learning platform used for quizzes and interactive learning.\n\n13. **StudyBlue** (www.studyblue.com) - A study platform that allows students to create and share study materials, such as flashcards and notes.\n\n14. **Ted-Ed** (www.ed.ted.com) - Features educational videos and lessons, offering innovative and engaging content across various subjects.\n\n15. **Zotero** (www.zotero.org) - A free reference manager that helps student collect, organize, cite, and share research sources.\n\n16. **Microsoft OneNote** (www.onenote.com) - A note-taking application that allows students to organize their notes, collaborate, and sync across devices.\n\nThese websites can help students with studying, collaboration, research, and resource gathering throughout their academic journey. Different resources may be more suitable depending on individual needs and subjects of study.",
